gomodel:SYNGO_1692  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In figure 1D the authors use an antibody against amphiphysin to demonstrate that the protein is localized pre-synaptically in mouse cortical neurons in culture. The specificity of the antibody is shown by lack of staining in an amphiphysin knockout mouse. In the additional literature I cite a paper using electron microscopy in lamprey demonstrating that lamprey amphiphysin is found on membranes of the endocytic zone following stimulation.. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"We have now generated amphiphysin 1 knockout mice...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-15" ;
